	<element name="Corruption" type="Class Feature" source="Mythical Conquest" id="ID_MYTHIC_CLASS_DIABOLIST_FEATURE_CORRUPTION">
		<description>
			<p>At 2nd level, you can take on the corruptive power of your covenant to bolster your own capabilities. As a Bonus Action, you enter a state of Corruption that lasts 1 minute or until the remove curse spell is cast. While Corrupted, your weapon attacks deal additional damage based on your Covenant equal to half of your Constitution Modifier for each consecutive turn you’ve been corrupted. Taking on this dark power has its drawbacks, however. While Corrupted, any hit points you regain are reduced by 1d4 for each consecutive turn you’ve been corrupted. You can use this feature twice per long rest, gaining more uses at 5th, 10th, and 16th level.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet action="Bonus Action" usage="{{diabolist_corruption:count}}/Long Rest">
			<description>
				<p>Enter a state of Corruption that lasts 1 minute or until the remove curse spell is cast. While Corrupted, your weapon attacks deal +{{constitution:modifier:half}} {{diabolist-covenant:damage_type}} damage for each consecutive turn you’ve been corrupted. While Corrupted, any hit points you regain are reduced by 1d4 for each consecutive turn you’ve been corrupted.</p>
			</description>
		</sheet>
